  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Forming a quadratic expression from consecutive numbers</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Two integers are represented by \(x\) and \( (x + {@k@}) \). Form and simplify an expression for their product.
</p>
<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The two numbers are:
</p>

<p>
\[
x \quad \text{and} \quad x + {@k@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Their product is:
</p>

<p>
\[
x(x + {@k@})
\]
</p>

<p>
Multiply \(x\) by both terms in the bracket:
</p>

<p>
\[
x \cdot x + x \cdot {@k@} = x^2 + {@k@}x
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the simplified product is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{x^2 + {@k@}x}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
